The National Drug Law Enforcement Agency (NDLEA) on Thursday filed a court application seeking the extension of the detention of the suspended Deputy Commissioner of Police, Abba Kyari and four other suspects involved in an alleged drug deal. The extension is for the agency to investigate the assets Kyari claimed to own in a viral video.  Abba Kyari confessed to the ownership of the choice estates in Lekki, Victoria Island, Lagos; Gussappe and Highbrow Asokoro in the Federal Capital Territory, Abuja, Vanguard reports. It was learnt that NDLEA operatives gave him an asset verification form to fill and are attempting to verify the properties he claimed he claimed were his in the video. It was also learnt that forensic analysis of the exhibits recovered from the suspects and other accomplices was done to get more suspects involved in the cocaine deal arrested.



